<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-594] cross-store=&gt; Define document name using annotation</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-594</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a cross-store configuration, the RelatedDocument is stored in a MongoDB collection using the container&apos;s Entity&apos;s package name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if the collection name would be either the name of the class (document, not entity) or as specified using annotations(@Document(collection=&quot;&quot;)).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This &quot;issue&quot; is caused by the class&lt;br/&gt;
org.springframework.data.mongodb.crossstore.MongoChangeSetPersister&lt;br/&gt;
which gets the name of the collection from the method getCollectionNameForEntity which does:&lt;br/&gt;
return ClassUtils.getQualifiedName(entityClass);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7 x64&lt;br/&gt;
jdk1.6.0_37 x64&lt;br/&gt;
Eclipse Juno x64</environment>
